TopicTitle: [1.3.0] [Kopernicus] Interstellar Adventure Revived v1.2.9 - A Taste of the Upcoming Grand Update! [18August17]

Articles.Content: Hey guys, I am looking for a mod that adds more solar systems. I tried KSS and GN, and now want to try this IAR - but I saw several posts back in this thread, saying that IAR peaks up RAM usage (and I already have very heavily modded install, and very little spare RAM), so my question is, is it worth even trying then? With KSS, I had game load times up to 15-20 minutes. Is IAR going to be the same in that regard?  Is it heavy on RAM?

having an issue as well.  Upgraded from 1.3 to 1.3.1, all mods were tested individually to make sure they worked w 1.3.1.  i also got the forever loading screen when I reinstalled IAR.  Also tried using an older ver of kopernicus just incase but i know that its game version specific.  anyone have any ideas or experience the same issue?

13 minutes ago, Diggz81 said:

having an issue as well.  Upgraded from 1.3 to 1.3.1, all mods were tested individually to make sure they worked w 1.3.1.  i also got the forever loading screen when I reinstalled IAR.  Also tried using an older ver of kopernicus just incase but i know that its game version specific.  anyone have any ideas or experience the same issue?

IAR is known to completely break in KSP 1.3.1 unless I'm mistaken. The dev is aware. 

On 12/10/2017 at 3:04 PM, aluc24 said:

Hey guys, I am looking for a mod that adds more solar systems. I tried KSS and GN, and now want to try this IAR - but I saw several posts back in this thread, saying that IAR peaks up RAM usage (and I already have very heavily modded install, and very little spare RAM), so my question is, is it worth even trying then? With KSS, I had game load times up to 15-20 minutes. Is IAR going to be the same in that regard?  Is it heavy on RAM?

I have not installed this mod for myself recently, but it's not nearly gigantic in any way as KSS is so it should be easy on your RAM.

This mod eats ram, not because of any problem with the mod, but with the sheer scope of how many new stars, planets, and moons it adds.  I've thought about stripping it down manually to just TRAPPIST-1 and Thallo, but I'm waiting for a 1.3.1-compatible version.  Unfortunately there are terrain/biome issues with the planets which, at least in 1.3.0, prevented colonization of them, but hopefully that will be resolved in the update as well.

On 12/18/2017 at 8:28 PM, ss8913 said:

This mod eats ram, not because of any problem with the mod, but with the sheer scope of how many new stars, planets, and moons it adds.  I've thought about stripping it down manually to just TRAPPIST-1 and Thallo, but I'm waiting for a 1.3.1-compatible version.  Unfortunately there are terrain/biome issues with the planets which, at least in 1.3.0, prevented colonization of them, but hopefully that will be resolved in the update as well.

This mod is compatible with KSP 1.3.1, but just remember to use the latest version of Kopernicus.

I'm hoping to eventually give all the planets biomes and maybe convert their textures to .dds files, which take up MUCH less space that .png files. However, not only is that a huge undertaking, but with the recent death of my cat I'm not too sure when I'll get back to KSP modding. I have a lot of kerbal genocide "experiments" to get out of my system, which may or may not involve throwing kerbals down the Mohole.
Does anyone here know how to fix the Moho/Disk thing? I can't seem to find it in the file system.

Hello, I have problem with loading of this mod. The bar keeps loading to the end, and then is there a small icon of loading in the right-down edge. Problem is that it doesnt show the main menu.

Experience tells me it is bad practice for planet modders to include Kopernicus in their downloads. I also believe it's the Kopernicus dev's wish that Kopernicus not be bundled. It saves everyone a little trouble if the user always firstly goes to Kopernicus' download area and pick the version for their KSP. Or, it becomes clear much sooner whether there's a fault on the planet modder's side or the Kopernicus side.

As for this mod, it is not to be expected to work well beyond Kopernicus 1.3.0-4 as it dos not have sunlight curves which were introduced in Kopernicus 1.3.0-6. No curves = infinite light from every star.
